uded, along with entries that describe each animal's form, coloration, habitat, distribution, reproductive biology, and natural history. Color plates of more than 75 percent of the species also help to facilitate visual identification. This accessible and informative guide is the most comprehensive field guide available and will appeal to both novice sightseers and professional naturalists.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aAmphibianszIslands of the PacificvIdentification. 0aReptileszIslands of the PacificvIdentification. 7aSCIENCE / Life Sciences / Biology.2bisacsh  aamphibian species.  aamphibians.  aanimal biology.  abeginners guide.  acolor illustrations.  acomparative guide.  adiverse species.  aevolution.  afield guide.  aflora and fauna.  afrogs.  ahabitats.  alife sciences.  alizards.  anatural history.  anatural world.  anaturalists.  anonfiction.  aoceanic islands.  aoceanside.  apacific basin.  apacific islands.  areptile species.  areptiles.  ascientists.  asnakes.  aspecies identification.  asystematic overview.  aturtles.  azoologists.  azoology.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052027495240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052095540040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520955400423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520955400/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-UCY